text: Ingrid Marianne Lundquist (later Grane, 24 July 1931 - 10 April 2020) was a Swedish freestyle swimmer. She was born in Stockholm. Lundquist won a bronze medal in the 4 Ã— 100 m relay at the 1950 European Aquatics Championships. She competed at the 1948 and 1952 Olympics.
